The paper deals with lossless compression of correlated strings, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves algorithms for compression and decompression, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also mentions probabilistic algorithms, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and the use of Kolmogorov complexity, which is a concept in machine learning and computational linguistics (cs.LG).
